                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <desc type="GuestText">
                              <locus target="#1r">f. 1r</locus>: Unidentified prayer.</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <note>The note is written in a <ref target="#h2" type="hand">secondary
                                 hand</ref>; the text is abraded and hardly legible.</note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <desc type="ProtectivePrayer">
                              <locus from="1v" to="2r"/> Protective prayer.</desc>
                           <q xml:lang="gez">
                              በእድጋድ፡ ወሰለለሎነ፡ ዑራኤል፡ ሰዱያልስ፡ ሰሰንያልስ፡
                              ተማምዖዶሙ፡ መድፍን፡ ድፍን፡ ልበሙ፡ ወእድልም፡ አዕይንቲሆሙ፡ አድከም፡ ኃይሎሙ፡...</q>
                           <note> Partly illegible, written in a <ref target="#h3" type="hand">crude
                                 hand</ref>, similar but not the same as that of <ref target="#a1">Additio 1</ref>.</note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a3">
                           <desc type="CalendaricNote">
                              <locus target="#2v">ff. 2v-3r</locus>: Calendaric note containing
                              feast days of the Evangelists and disciples.</desc>
                           <q xml:lang="gez"> ሠረቀ፡ መስከረም፡ አመ፡ ፩በርተሎሜዎስ፡ ሐዋርያ። ሠረቀ፡ ጥቅምት፡ አመ፡ ፩ወሰኑዩ፡
                              ማቴዎስ፡ ሐዋርያ። አመ፡ ፳ወ፪ሉቃስ፡ ወንጌላዊ፡ ሠረቀ፡ ኅዳር፡ አመ፡ ፲ወ፰ፊልጶስ፡ ሐዋርያ።...</q>
                           <note> Written in black ink, in a <ref target="#h4" type="hand">secondary
                                 hand</ref> (neat, rounded, upright or slightly left-sloping
                              letters).</note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a4">
                           <desc type="ProtectivePrayer">
                              <locus target="#3r">ff. 3r-3v</locus> Protective prayer (containing
                                 ʾasmāt?).<q xml:lang="gez">
                                 <locus target="#3r">3r</locus>: በቃለ፡ እግዚአብሕር፡ አብ፡ ቆሔት፡ ወልድ፡ ቆሔት፡
                                 መንፈስ፡ ቅዱስ፡ ቆሔት፡ እንዘ፡ ፫፡ ፩ወእንዘ፡ ፩፫ቱ፡ ጺዱመ፡ ልጋመ፡ እሳት፡ አውላልኤል፡ ኀብዕ፡
                                 መለኮት፡ በዝንቱ፡ አስማቲከ...</q>
                               Written in the same <ref target="#h4" type="hand">hand</ref> as <ref target="#a3">Additio 3</ref>.</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a5">
                           <desc type="GuestText">
                              <locus target="#3v">ff. 3v-4r</locus>: Prayer for women against the
                              pain of childbirth.<q xml:lang="gez">
                                  በስመ፡ አብ፡ ወወልድ፡ ወመንፈስ፡ ቅዱስ፡ ፩አምላክ።
                                 ጸሎተ፡ ምሕረት፡ መላእክት፡ ወሰማዕት፡ ወጳጳሳት፡ ወቀሳውስት፡ ወሰዲያቆናተ፡ ዘጸለዩ፡ ዘንተ፡ ጸሎተ፡
                                 ብእንተ፡ ዕፁባት፡ አንስት፡ ...</q>
                               Written in the same <ref target="#h4">hand</ref> as <ref target="#a3">Additio 3</ref>. The prayer
                              invokes the angel <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS8083Raphael">Raphael (Rufāʾel)
                              </persName>to protect women from pain during labour. It might be the
                              same prayer as in Ms. EMML 4730 (f. 47a).</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a6">
                           <desc type="ProtectivePrayer">
                              <locus target="#4r">f. 4r</locus>: Protective prayer (containing
                                 ʾasmāt?).<q xml:lang="gez">
                                 በስመ፡ አብ፡ በል፡ ግርሙያል፡ ሽርሙያል፡ አናንያል፡
                                 አዘርያል፡ ተንሥአ፡ ማሰያስ፡ ወሲላሶ፡ እንዘ፡ ይቁረጥም፡ እደ፡ ወእግረ፡ ወኵሉ፡ አባለ፡ ሥጋሁ፡
                                 ለገብርከ፡ ዓምደ፡ ሚካል[sic]፡ ዘዮናስ፡ ዘዮናስ፡ ዘዮናስ፡ እንዘ፡ ደቁረጥም፡ እደ፡ ወእግረ፡ ወነፋሱ፡
                                 ለገብርከ፡ ዓምደ፡ ሚካኤል፡</q>
                               Written in a secondary <ref type="hand" target="#h5">hand</ref> in black and red ink. Prayer with ʾasmāt
                              for <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS11976AmdaMikael">ʾAmda Mikāʾel</persName>, the
                              owner of the Ms.</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a7">
                           <desc type="GuestText" corresp="LIT2765RepCh49">
                             Salutation for <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS7840Phanuel">Phanuel</persName> (salām la-Fānuʾel).<q xml:lang="gez">
                                 ሰላ፡ ለከ፡ ሰዳደ፡ አጋንንት፡ ፋኑኤል፡ ለእግዚአብሔር፡
                                 እምጽርሑ፡ ከመ፡ ኤይስክዩ፡ ሰብአ፡ እለ፡ ይኔሁ፡ ለጌጋይ፡ ዘዘኢአሁ።...</q>
                               Written in black and red ink, in the same <ref target="#h4">hand</ref> as <ref target="#a3">Additio 3</ref>. Cp.
                                 <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2765RepCh49">Malkǝʾ-hymn (Salām) to Phanuel</ref>. The abbreviation ሰላ፡
                              for ሰላም፡ is used.</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a8">
                           <desc type="GuestText">
                              <locus target="#5v">f. 5v-6r</locus>: Fragment of an unidentified
                                 text.<q xml:lang="gez"/>
                               The fols. seem to be taken from another, older,
                              Ms. The hand shows older features. The name <persName role="donor" cert="medium" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS11978TaklaHaymanotAgamyo">Takla
                                 Hāymānot</persName> is given, probably the donor?</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a9">
                           <desc type="OwnershipNote">
                              <locus target="#106vb">f. 106vb</locus>
                              <q xml:lang="gez"> ዝመጽሐፍ፡ ዘ[l.n.]ካኤል፡ እደ [l.n.]ገብረ፡ [l.n.]ወእሙ፡
                                 ወለተ፡ ራሔል፡ ለ [l.n.]ለመ፡ ዓለም</q> The note, partly illegible, is
                              crudely written by at least two different hands. From the pieces that
                              are legible we assume, that the book belongs to <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS11976AmdaMikael">ʾAmda Mikāʾel</persName>, and that his
                              father’s name is Gabra [l.n.] and his mother’s name is Walatta
                              Rāḥel.</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a10">
                           <desc type="GuestText">
                              <locus target="#107v">f. 107v</locus>: salām la-Fānuʾel. <q xml:lang="gez"> ሰላ፡ ሰላም፡ ነሀብ፡ ለለጌሠሙ፡ ስብሐተ፡ ፋኑኤል፡ ...</q>
                               Written in black and red ink, in the same <ref target="#h4">hand</ref> as <ref target="#a3">Additio 3</ref>. The
                              prayer is partly illegible. It might be the continuation of <ref target="#a7">Additio 7</ref>. The abbreviation ሰላ፡ for ሰላም፡ is
                              used.</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1"><desc>- The name of <persName role="owner" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS11974WaldaAnanya">Walda ʾAnānyā</persName> is written in red in a supplication
                           formula over an erasue, on <locus target="#50rb">50rb</locus>.</desc></item>
                        <item xml:id="e2"><desc>- Ethiopic numerals are crudely written in pencil in the
                           upper margins at the beginnings of quires (starting at quire IX): <locus target="#63r">63r</locus>, 71r, 79, 95.</desc> </item>
                        <item xml:id="e3"><desc> - At the incipit page of <ref target="#ms_i2">Text
                              II</ref> (<locus target="#65vb">65vb</locus>), a directive concerning
                           the use of the text is written in the upper margin: <foreign xml:lang="gez">ከለአተ፡ ድግመ፡ ዝንቱ፡ ኢትህድጉ</foreign>
                           “Do not forget to read this twice”. </desc></item>
                        <item xml:id="e4"><desc>- Text has been erased on <locus target="#107r">107r</locus> and a cross has been painted over it.</desc></item>
                        <item xml:id="e5">
                           <desc type="findingAid">- Red threads are inserted in the right upper corner
                              of fols. 17, 42, 61, 79. </desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e6">
                           <desc type="findingAid">- In Text I daily readings are indicated by
                              the names of the days written in the upper margin of some fols.,
                              encircled by dots: za-sanuy (<locus target="#7ra">fol. 7ra</locus>)
                              za-salus (<locus target="#16va">fol. 16va</locus>) za-rabuʾǝ (<locus target="#21vb">fol. 21vb</locus>) za-ḥamus (<locus target="#30va">fol. 30va</locus>) za-ʾarb (<locus target="#42vb">fol.
                                 42vb</locus>) za-qadām[sic] (<locus target="#54ra">fol.
                                 54ra</locus>) za-ʾǝhud (<locus target="#61rb">fol. 61rb</locus>).
                              The daily divisions mostly correspond with the “chapters” introduced
                              in <bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/W2T69F7J"><seg type="journalArticle"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:Littmann1904Ardeet"/><title level="a">Ardeʾet: The Magic Book of the Disciples</title><title level="j">Journal of the American Oriental Society</title><author><forename>Enno</forename><surname>Littmann</surname></author><date>1904</date><biblScope unit="volume">25</biblScope><biblScope unit="page">1-48</biblScope><note type="url">https://archive.org/details/jstor-592548</note><note type="tags"><note type="tag">Book of the Disciples</note><note type="tag">bm:Littmann1904Ardeet</note></note><note type="tag">Book of the Disciples</note><note type="tag">bm:Littmann1904Ardeet</note></bibl>).</desc>
                        </item>
                     </list>
                  </additions>
                  <bindingDesc>
                     <binding contemporary="false">
                        <decoNote xml:id="b1">Two wooden boards.
 Two pairs of sewing
                           stations.</decoNote>
                        <decoNote xml:id="b2" type="bindingMaterial">
                           <material key="wood"/>
                        </decoNote>
