               <history>
                  <origin>
                     <origPlace>
                        <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/INS0093AGM">ʾAgamyo Qǝddus Mikāʾel</placeName>
                     </origPlace>
                     <origDate notBefore="1800" notAfter="1900">19th century (?).
 Quire I is
                        possibly of earlier age (?).</origDate>
                  </origin>
                  <provenance>The Ms. is currently (<date>2010</date>) in private possession of
                        <persName role="owner" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS11977Gayyem">qašši Gāyyǝm</persName>
                     (ʾAgāmyo). Two names are mentioned (added by a secondary hand) in the
                     supplication formulas, <persName role="owner" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS11975AmdaMaryam">ʾAmda
                        Māryām</persName> (<locus target="#19ra">19ra</locus>, <locus target="#20rb">20rb</locus>, <locus target="#25vb">25vb</locus>, etc.) and <persName role="owner" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS11976AmdaMikael">ʾAmda Mikāʾel</persName> (<locus target="#20rb">20rb</locus>, 21rb, etc.). <persName role="owner" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS11975AmdaMaryam">ʾAmda Māryām</persName> might be the original
                     owner, as it appears in <locus target="#20rb">20rb</locus>, 47ra, 48vb, etc.
                     Several times the owner’s name was erased, e.g., <locus target="#12vb">12vb</locus>, 13rb, 21rb, 21vb, etc. On <locus target="#106vb">106vb</locus> the parents of <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS11976AmdaMikael">ʾAmda
                        Mikāʾel</persName> are mentioned, his father Gabra (...) and his mother
                     Walatta Rāḥel.</provenance>
